Reasoning: The paper deals with a fundamental problem in data structures, specifically static predecessor searching, and studies it in the cell probe model introduced by Yao. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses tools from information theory and communication complexity, indicating that it may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new type of query scheme called `quantum address-only' and extends its results to quantum communication complexity, suggesting that it may belong to the cs.QI (Quantum Information) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a new round elimination lemma that may have other applications, indicating that it may also belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category.
